`nvim/` is the Neovim-side consumer of the steno-ts theory compiler's
build output: it turns `@@token@@` sentinels (typed by Plover via a
generated stroke dictionary) into real LSP snippets with tabstops. A
reader one level up gets a self-contained plugin directory plus its
README describing the external contract; there's no other code at this
level.

The whole implementation is one hop down, in `lua/steno-ts/` (reachable
via `lua/`), which owns the sentinel format, the `M.setup(opts)` entry
point, and the runtime dependency on two paired JSON artifacts
(`plover-keys.json`, `snippets.json`) produced together by
`build-nvim` — regenerating one without the other breaks token matching.
The README documents the external contract and a known, accepted
limitation (stray characters on chained type-append expansions through
non-terminal heads, caused by Plover's retro-delete counting original
token length rather than expanded length); this is not something to "fix"
inside the Lua code without addressing it at the Plover/compiler
boundary.

No intent.md exists here, so there is nothing to check for divergence.